Data Cloud Reports and Dashboards: Limits and Limitations

These limits and limitations apply to Data Cloud reports and dashboards.

Data Cloud Reports Limits:
- Number of Rows Displayed: 2,000 rows in run mode.
- Row-level Formulas: 1 formula supported per report.
 
Report Features Not Available:
- Custom report types on Calculated Insights
- Stacked summaries
- Change granularity level on grouped date fields
- Standard filters cross filters, filter by scope, filter by dimension values
- Inline editing
- Open report in Quip
- Einstein Discovery for Reports
- Reports on Experience Cloud Sites
- Subscribe to Data Cloud reports in Slack
- Joined reports
- Bucket column
- Support for multiple currencies
- Support for custom fiscal periods
- Row limit filters in a tabular report
- Historical trending
- Trend in Wave report snapshots

Functions Not Available:
- ISCLONE, ISNEW, ISNULL, ISNUMBER, NOT, NULLVALUE, OR, PARENTGROUPVAL, PREGROUPVAL, PRIORVALUE.
 
Considerations When Using Data Cloud Reports:
- Subtotals are included in the row limit.
- Totals and subtotals based on all report data.
- Can't export details-only report as .xlsx file.
- Salesforce Identity licenses restrict access to Data Cloud reports.
- Static formulas and grouped columns aren't supported in custom summary formulas.
title: Data Cloud Reports and Dashboards Limits
